land, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Llandegai, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Llandegai, Caernarfonshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Essex, England":"Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Kidderminster, Worcester, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1523–1549":"1523–1549","1515–1564":"1515–1564","1544–1590":"1544–1590","1500–1543":"1500–1543","1500–1523":"1500–1523","14 Jun 1549-1552":"from 14 June 1549 to 1552","1523":"1523","1544":"1544","1522":"1522","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","20 February 1523":"20 February 1523","1590":"1590","1549":"1549","1515":"1515",", , Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom","Exmouth, East Devon, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Exmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Llandegai, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Llandegai, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","Kidderminster, Worcester, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wordle","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Woodall   or   Weddell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Woodall","meanings":["English (mainly West Midlands): from Middle English <i>wode</i> ‘wood’ + <i>halle</i> ‘hall’ (Old English <i>wudu</i> + <i>hall</i>). The surname may be topographic, for a person who lived at a hall in a wood, or habitational, from one of the many places so named, such as Woodhall (Lincolnshire), Woodhall Farm in Wichenford (Worcestershire), Wood Hall in Risley (Derbyshire), Woodhall in Calverley (Yorkshire), or Woodall in Harthill (Yorkshire)."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":26,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Wordle was born in 1523, in Exmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Wordle, was 23 and her mother, Jane Elizabeth Stradling, was 23. She married Thomas Rose in 1543, in Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1549, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 26, and was buried in Wiltshire, England."},"et":{"1523–1549":"1523–1549","1515–1564":"1515–1564","1544–1590":"1544–1590","1500–1543":"1500–1543","1500–1523":"1500–1523","14 Jun 1549-1552":"14. juuni 1549 kuni 1552","1523":"1523","1544":"1544","1522":"1522","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","20 February 1523":"20. veebruar 1523","1590":"1590","1549":"1549","1515":"1515",", , Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Exmouth, East Devon, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Exmouth, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Llandegai, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Llandegai, Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kidderminster, Worcester, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1523–1549":"1523–1549","1515–1564":"1515–1564","1544–1590":"1544–1590","1500–1543":"1500–1543","1500–1523":"1500–1523","14 Jun 1549-1552":"vuodesta 14. kesäkuuta 1549 vuoteen 1552","1523":"1523","1544":"1544","1522":"1522","1500":"1500","1543":"1543","1564":"1564","20 February 1523":"20. helmikuuta 1523","1590":"1590","1549":"1549","1515":"1515",", , Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Exmouth, East Devon, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Exmouth, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, England","Llandegai, Caernarvonshire, Wales":"Llandegai, Caernarfonshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Penrhyn Castle, Caernarfonshire, Wales","Essex, England":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kun